  (2, 'Wakapoa', 'partial', 50, '2 water systems currently: A new water system was constructed on the Secondary & Primary School Island in 2024. This serves approximately 20 houses, the schools, health center and other government buildings. A new water system was constructed in Mora in early 2026 which supplies approximately 60 households and surrounding residents.', 'New water systems to be constructed in-house in the second half of 2026 and in 2027 to provide increased coverage.', 'Community is made up of many islands. School Island System in working order; Mora well started to produced sand and burnt pump   (contractor to remobilising to address this by July 5)', NULL, NULL),
  (2, 'Akawini', 'partial', 95, 'Community has 4 wells, 3 wells were drilled in 2024/2025 by GWI inhouse team and an old 4 inch well by the school. The community is made up of 3 major areas. The remaining population is scattered across the reservation.', 'GWI Continue to monitor and maintain along with village council', 'System powered by solar; Some residents complain about low pressure sometimes. All systems are in working order but leaks and wastages usually affect the further sections', NULL, NULL),
